@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 DLError is an errors-administrator between DICE Pro and GoldED.


 It  allow you to index compilation-errors in a window, and you can go quicky
 to errors by clicking on it.


 DLError  drive  GoldED  with  Arexx, but GoldED can also drive DLError (next
 error, quit DLError..) with Arexx too.


 When  you  compile with DICE, if there is an error, a window with a listview
 is openned and GoldED too in the same time. Then you have just to  click  on
 an error for GoldED to go to it.


 This package contain an Arexx script for GoldED to  send  Arexx  command  to
 DLError, and there is also an Arexx Script for GoldED to drive DICE Help.


 DLError was tested with GoldED release 3 but it will  work  with  minor  and
 superior version, if its Arexx commands are the same.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Arexx"
@prev "Introduction"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}@{u}@{fg shine}For use DLError:@{ub}@{uu}@{fg text}

    o Copy DLError in DCC:BIN.

    o Overwrite  DCC:Config/DCC.config  by  Config/DCC.config  archived  in the
      package,

      Or modify it yourself:

        dcc.config:
            [ ....]
            cmd = DCC:BIN/DLErr or %e
            linkcmd= DCC:BIN/DLErr or %e

      It's this file which allows DLError to run when there are some compilation
      errors.

    o Be sure than GoldED is installed, DLError try  to  run  the quickstarter
      'GoldED:ED'.

    o Copy the 2 Arexx scripts (DLE_Func.ged et DiceHelp.ged) in GoldED:ARexx.


 @{u}In GoldED, I have modified keyboard config in order to drive DLError:@{uu}


   @{i}@{fg shine}Close the window of GoldED and DLError@{ui}@{fg text}

    o Shift-F9 :    (DOS)       rx GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged QUIT
                    (INTERN)    QUIT


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DLError for going to the first error@{ui}@{fg text}

    o F1 :          (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged FIRST


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DLError for going to the last error@{ui}@{fg text}

    o Shift-F1:     (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged LAST


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DLError for going to the next error@{ui}@{fg text}

    o F2:           (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged NEXT


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DLError for going to the previous error@{ui}@{fg text}

    o Shift-F2      (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged PREV


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DLError for going to the current error@{ui}@{fg text}

    o F3            (AREXX)    GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged CURRENT


   @{i}@{fg shine}Ask DICE Help  for the current word@{ui}@{fg text}

    o F5            (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DiceHelp.ged


   @{i}@{fg shine}DLError's window will go to front@{ui}@{fg text}

    o F10           (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged WindowToFront


   @{i}@{fg shine}DLError's window will go to back@{ui}@{fg text}

    o Shift-F10     (AREXX)     GoldED:Arexx/DLE_Func.ged WindowToBack



 DLError use the @{"bgui.library" link "Copyrights" 0} for it's GUI.
@endnode

@node "Arexx" "Arexx"
@next "Menus & GUI"
@prev "Installation"
@{b}@{u}Arexx@{ub}@{uu}

 o The Arexx port of DLError is DLERROR.xx (DLERROR.01 for the first..).

 o DLError arexx commands:

      WindowToFront         The window of DLError will go to front.
                            (If flags 'Window activate' is on, the window
                            will go to front, and will be activate).

      WindowToBack          The window of DLError will go to back.

      QUIT                  Quit DLError :-((


   These commands are for the positionning on the  errors,  for  each  DLError
   will send to GoldED arexx command for going to errors.


    CURRENT                 Go to current error
    NEXT                    Go to the next error
    PREV                    Go to the previous error
    FIRST                   Go to the first error
    LAST                    Go to the last error


 o Arexx command send to GoldED (Can not be yet configure):

    OPEN NAME <filename>            Open file
    GOTO LINE <xx> COLUMN <yy>      Go to...

    LOCK CURRENT                    Lock the window while loading
    UNLOCK                          Unlock the window
@endnode

@node "Menus & GUI" "Menus & GUI"
@next "Disclaimer"
@prev "Arexx"
@{b}@{u}GUI@{ub}@{uu}

        Button 'ReLoad file':       Ask GoldED for reloading the current file,
                                    and going to the current error.

        Button 'Close All':         Ask  GoldED  for  closing it's window  and
                                    ending of DLError .

@{b}@{u}Menus@{ub}@{uu}

        Project
             
            About...                Information on the program and the
                                    author.

             
            Save Prefs              Save the prefs of DLError
                                    (DCC:Config/DLError.prefs).

             
            Reload file             See above.

             
            Close All               See above.

             
            Quit                    Quit DLError.


        Prefs

             
            Snapshot window         Snapshot the DLError window.

             
            Unsnapshot window       Unsnapshot the DLError window.

             
            Activate window         Ask DLError for activating  it's window
                                    when DLError open it or  when the Arexx
                                    command WindowToFront is receive.

             
            Snapshot on quit        Always snapshot the DLError window when
                                    DLError quit.
@endnode

